In addition, time-resolved fluorescence lifetime measurements were performed for GQDs and Tb-GQDs with the absence and presence of melamine (Fig. 3
                        ). Table 1
                         provides the lifetime variations relative to dopant and adulterant. The decay curve of nanocomposites and Melamine complexes is well-fitted with a tri-exponential function. The obtained average lifetime of GQD is 2.9 ns [6.25 ns (33.2 %), 1.11 ns (34.6 %), and 1.465 ns (32.2 %)], and it increases to 9.34 ns [7.95 ns (30.7 %), 0.145 ns (42.7 %), and 2064 ns (26.7 %)] when terbium was doped to it. Further, the average lifetime of Tb-GQD slightly decreases from 9.34 ns to 7.89 ns in the presence of melamine, confirming the improved detection efficiency of Melamine by Tb-GQDs.
